1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,545
[Artillero] <i>Do not say anything</i>
<i>aggressive against the women.</i>

2
00:00:03,628 --> 00:00:05,046
<i>If we control the narrative,</i>

3
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:07,132
<i>we can show the court</i>
<i>there is reasonable doubt.</i>

4
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:08,133
<i>That's easy.</i>

5
00:00:10,218 --> 00:00:12,470
[Alba] <i>I'm confident we will win.</i>

6
00:00:12,554 --> 00:00:15,015
<i>You are fighting for abused women.</i>

7
00:00:15,098 --> 00:00:17,225
<i>Do you know what you are giving them?</i>

8
00:00:17,308 --> 00:00:18,184
<i>Hope.</i>

9
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:20,770
[Alice]<i> If something's going</i>
<i>on between you and Lucas,</i>

10
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:21,855
<i>you have to tell Mel.</i>

11
00:00:21,938 --> 00:00:23,565
<i>The way you two are, when you're together,</i>

12
00:00:23,648 --> 00:00:24,607
<i>it's not nothing.</i>

13
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:26,109
<i>So it's not Kyle.</i>

14
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:27,402
<i>Here we go again.</i>

15
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:30,405
<i>We just keep going in circles,</i>
<i>and it always leads us back to Edong.</i>

16
00:00:30,488 --> 00:00:32,240
<i>You've been there all along,</i>

17
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:34,409
<i>deceiving everyone</i>
<i>into thinking you're normal.</i>

18
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:37,120
<i>You can't stop me</i>
<i>from getting them. </i>[chuckles]

19
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:38,079
<i>I can't!</i>

20
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:41,041
<i>It’s like my brain won’t let</i>
<i>me remember what happened.</i>

21
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:44,127
<i>It's protecting you from something</i>
<i>you are not ready to deal with.</i>

22
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:47,213
<i>What else is there to know</i>
<i>that could devastate me even more?</i>

23
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:48,173
<i>What the fuck was that?!</i>

24
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:50,842
<i>I thought I went there</i>
<i>because they'd side with me!</i>

25
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:52,594
<i>Lucas, Mom. I still love him.</i>

26
00:00:52,677 --> 00:00:54,220
<i>I don't know what to do.</i>

27
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:55,513
<i>So? Did you do it?</i>

28
00:00:55,597 --> 00:01:00,351
<i>Of course, sir.</i>
<i>For that much money, I can do anything.</i>

29
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:04,689
- [keyboard clacking]
- [suspenseful music playing]

30
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:08,943
[clicking, whirring]

31
00:01:09,027 --> 00:01:10,528
[keyboard clacking]

32
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:15,533
[clicking, clacking]

33
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:20,497
[suspenseful music continues]

34
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:29,380
[clacking, whirring]

35
00:01:30,715 --> 00:01:37,263
[theme music playing]

36
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:50,086
[unsettling music playing]

37
00:02:50,169 --> 00:02:51,921
[gasps, breath quivers]

38
00:02:54,465 --> 00:02:56,926
[Tom's breath quivering]

39
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:58,636
[whispers] Oh my god.

40
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,473
[panicked breaths] Oh my God.

41
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:03,516
Hey.

42
00:03:04,225 --> 00:03:05,310
What happened?

43
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:07,645
Mel, oh my god!

44
00:03:08,396 --> 00:03:09,564
What is it?

45
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:12,817
[music becomes uneasy]

46
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:14,110
What?

47
00:03:24,787 --> 00:03:29,042
[uneasy music builds]

48
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:38,134
[Mel breathing heavily]

49
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:39,969
Oh my god.

50
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:45,433
This isn't me!

51
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,478
This is not me!

52
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:53,274
[uneasy music continues]

53
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:03,201
[whimpers, gags]

54
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:05,536
- [retching]
- [Tim] Mel.

55
00:04:06,162 --> 00:04:08,039
[Tom] Oh my god, what do we do?

56
00:04:08,122 --> 00:04:09,415
[Mel coughs]

57
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:14,587
[sobbing]

58
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,631
It's not me!

59
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:18,967
[continues sobbing]

60
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:20,176
[music fades]

61
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,512
I don't encourage you to keep digging.

62
00:04:23,471 --> 00:04:26,015
[solemn music playing]

63
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:27,767
Your body is warning us.

64
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:30,436
Don't force your memory back.

65
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:32,188
Doc…

66
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:34,649
No, no. Please.

67
00:04:35,149 --> 00:04:36,317
We can't stop.

68
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:39,362
I- I have to do this.
You know I need to do this.

69
00:04:40,822 --> 00:04:41,781
[sighs]

70
00:04:43,157 --> 00:04:44,909
I'll think about it, Alice.

71
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:50,456
[phone ringing]

72
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:52,208
[music fades]

73
00:04:52,834 --> 00:04:53,793
Hello?

74
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:57,088
[Edward] She is still my favorite.

75
00:04:57,171 --> 00:05:01,509
[ominous music playing]

76
00:05:03,845 --> 00:05:04,887
[program playing on TV]

77
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:06,514
[man]<i> Whoa!</i>

78
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:12,020
[program continues]

79
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:13,896
[boy]<i> Ma, look at the Ferris wheel!</i>

80
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:16,816
[mother]<i> You're right.</i>

81
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:19,777
<i>Riding a Ferris wheel</i>
<i>is like riding a carabao,</i>

82
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:23,197
<i>but it's safer</i>
<i>because it won't fall apart!</i>

83
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:26,284
<i>And you won't get</i>
<i>dizzy from all the spinning.</i>

84
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:30,663
<i>Son, a carabao can take you places.</i>

85
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:32,498
<i>Far away places.</i>

86
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:36,377
[hopeful music playing on TV]

87
00:05:37,628 --> 00:05:43,217
[sinister music playing]

88
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:50,058
- [water splashes]
- [carabao moos]

89
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:51,934
[men laughing]

90
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:52,977
[man] <i>Oh.</i>

91
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:54,103
- [men laughing]
- [man] <i>Oh!</i>

92
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:55,605
[laughter continues]

93
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:57,732
- [carabao moos]
<i>- </i>[man] <i>What happened?</i>

94
00:05:57,815 --> 00:05:58,816
<i>Whoo!</i>

95
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:02,278
<i>I don't think your son</i>
<i>has a future in farming, Jun!</i>

96
00:06:02,361 --> 00:06:04,238
<i>- Come on.</i>
<i>- </i>[Jun] <i>Huh?</i>

97
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:05,281
[man chuckles]

98
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:07,325
- [boy] Papa?
- [Jun]<i> Oh?</i>

99
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:09,118
[boy] Mama said that…

100
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:10,119
[Jun]<i> What?</i>

101
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:12,663
[boy] <i>She said, riding a carabao</i>

102
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:15,166
<i>is like riding a Ferris wheel!</i>

103
00:06:15,249 --> 00:06:16,793
- [Jun chuckles]
- [music fades]

104
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:17,877
Hello?

105
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:20,088
Lemuel?

106
00:06:21,255 --> 00:06:22,340
Anybody home?

107
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:29,263
Oh! Lucas, what are you doing here?

108
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:30,807
I'm here to help.

109
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:34,435
Do you even know why I'm here?

110
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:35,603
Yes.

111
00:06:35,686 --> 00:06:37,647
That's the house of
Louisa's brother, right?

112
00:06:39,357 --> 00:06:41,567
You're here to find out

113
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:46,072
if he knows anyone
who had motive to hurt Louisa.

114
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:49,075
[sighs softly]

115
00:06:49,158 --> 00:06:51,494
When I first tried, he cursed me out.

116
00:06:53,663 --> 00:06:54,956
Yet here you are again.

117
00:06:56,707 --> 00:06:57,917
I'm used to it.

118
00:06:58,626 --> 00:07:01,254
I think I’ve heard
every kind of insult there is.

119
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,840
Some come from anger.

120
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:06,509
Words meant to tear you apart.

121
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:08,886
Some come from hunger.

122
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,889
From the empty stomachs of the poor.

123
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:15,435
And then there are insults from the rich.

124
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:18,521
Ah, like they'd say, "Fuck you!"

125
00:07:20,481 --> 00:07:21,524
No.

126
00:07:22,942 --> 00:07:24,444
Polite on the tongue,

127
00:07:24,902 --> 00:07:26,779
but poisonous underneath.

128
00:07:26,863 --> 00:07:28,948
You know what kind of
filth a politician would shout?

129
00:07:30,324 --> 00:07:31,242
What?

130
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:32,910
"For the people!"

131
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:36,914
[chuckles softly]

132
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:43,671
"You're number one in my heart."

133
00:07:44,338 --> 00:07:47,467
[soft music playing]

134
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:51,345
"So make sure I'm first
on your list of people to vote!"

135
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:56,517
[chuckles, scoffs]

136
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:02,690
Some insults aren't spoken at all.

137
00:08:04,108 --> 00:08:07,153
You feel them
the moment you turn your back,

138
00:08:07,945 --> 00:08:09,155
in the way people look at you.

139
00:08:09,238 --> 00:08:12,533
[soft music continues]

140
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:15,953
I've been insulted and
cursed at so many times.

141
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:19,832
I'm sure…

142
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:24,420
You have too.

143
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:29,425
[soft music continues]

144
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:31,511
It's okay. You can tell me.

145
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:36,349
Words can't hurt me anymore.

146
00:08:37,391 --> 00:08:42,271
[soft music swells]

147
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:44,357
I didn't think…

148
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:48,152
we were still capable of smiling.

149
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:52,657
[soft music continues]

150
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:55,368
[Alice] <i>Mel saw you two last night.</i>

151
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:56,869
<i>You and Lucas.</i>

152
00:08:57,411 --> 00:08:58,955
<i>We were just talking, Alice.</i>

153
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:00,373
<i>Oh, come on, Erika.</i>

154
00:09:00,456 --> 00:09:02,458
<i>And the way you two</i>
<i>are when you're together,</i>

155
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:03,793
<i>it's not nothing.</i>

156
00:09:04,335 --> 00:09:06,128
<i>We both know it.</i>

157
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:08,506
<i>We've already had</i>
<i>this conversation before.</i>

158
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:13,678
[soft music continues, fades]

159
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:19,350
[uneasy music playing]

160
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:20,309
Lemuel.

161
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:24,272
[music fades]

162
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:26,190
So, how's your search for Edong going?

163
00:09:27,441 --> 00:09:28,484
[sighs softly]

164
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:32,613
We've searched those
areas countless times already.

165
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:35,658
We even checked
places that aren't on the map.

166
00:09:36,117 --> 00:09:37,702
Edong's smart.

167
00:09:39,036 --> 00:09:40,580
We can't find him.

168
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:43,040
[sighs]

169
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:45,793
He's just a man.

170
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:49,338
We'll find him eventually.

171
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,757
[foreboding music playing]

172
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:53,050
[sighs heavily]

173
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,052
I'll go look around.

174
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:56,804
I'll call if I find anything.

175
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:58,014
Thanks.

176
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:00,391
[music fades]

177
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:02,143
I heard you.

178
00:10:02,226 --> 00:10:07,440
You were talking
about Liezel Basa and Louisa?

179
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:10,484
I didn't even know that…

180
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:13,070
that happened to my sister.

181
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:15,948
I wish she had told me.

182
00:10:19,368 --> 00:10:20,828
She didn't tell anyone.

183
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:23,456
Even us.

184
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,127
She was trying to protect Liezel

185
00:10:29,086 --> 00:10:30,796
from her pastor father.

186
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:31,964
[scoffs]

187
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:36,761
She protected everyone but herself.

188
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:40,806
[Lemuel sighs]

189
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:42,016
She was the youngest,

190
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:44,477
but she was…

191
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:48,939
more mature than Lester and I,
her older brothers.

192
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:56,405
[unsettling music playing]

193
00:10:57,406 --> 00:11:00,242
[distant clamoring]

194
00:11:03,537 --> 00:11:08,376
[clamoring continues to swell]

195
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:12,505
[crowd jeering]

196
00:11:12,588 --> 00:11:13,798
<i>- Hit him!</i>
<i>- Lester!</i>

197
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:15,091
<i>- Lester!</i>
- [blow lands]

198
00:11:15,174 --> 00:11:17,760
<i>- Back off!</i>
<i>- Lester! Lester, enough!</i>

199
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:21,389
<i>- Lester! Lester!</i>
<i>- Hit him! Hit him!</i>

200
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:23,682
<i>- Alright!</i>
- [Louisa] <i>Stop it, Lester!</i>

201
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:25,643
<i>Lester! Please!</i>

202
00:11:26,143 --> 00:11:28,604
<i>- Enough, Lester!</i>
- [blows land]

203
00:11:28,687 --> 00:11:32,441
- [blows landing]
<i>- Get up! Get up! Nice!</i>

204
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,734
<i>- Alright!</i>
<i>- Knock him out!</i>

205
00:11:34,151 --> 00:11:35,069
[blows land]

206
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:36,237
<i>Lester!</i>

207
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,863
- [blows landing]
<i>- Move!</i>

208
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:41,200
<i>- Lester, enough!</i>
- [blows land]

209
00:11:41,283 --> 00:11:42,243
<i>- Aah!</i>
- [young Lemuel] <i>Louisa!</i>

210
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:43,953
- [body thuds]
- [blow lands]

211
00:11:44,036 --> 00:11:45,996
<i>- Louisa!</i>
- [Louisa breathing heavily]

212
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,248
[punches landing]

213
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:48,874
- [watchman] <i>Hey! Enough!</i>
<i>- Let him be!</i>

214
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:51,544
<i>- Lester, enough! Please!</i>
<i>- Hey!</i>

215
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:53,129
<i>- Aah!</i>
<i>- Hey!</i>

216
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:55,256
<i>- Get him!</i>
<i>- You don't want to stop?!</i>

217
00:11:55,339 --> 00:11:56,424
- [Louisa] <i>Lester!</i>
- [thwacks]

218
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:58,134
<i>- You think you're tough?!</i>
- [thwacking]

219
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:00,636
<i>- Sir, stop it!</i>
<i>- Not so tough now, huh?</i>

220
00:12:00,719 --> 00:12:02,471
<i>- Enough, please!</i>
- [thwacks, grunts]

221
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:03,848
<i>Sir, please!</i>

222
00:12:05,474 --> 00:12:06,725
[panting]

223
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:08,769
<i>Miss Cheska? Miss Cheska!</i>

224
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:11,439
<i>I'm begging you,</i>
<i>please don't press charges against Lester.</i>

225
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:13,274
<i>My son almost died</i>

226
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:14,567
<i>because your brother beat him up!</i>

227
00:12:15,025 --> 00:12:16,444
<i>I'm apologizing on his behalf.</i>

228
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:19,613
<i>Miss Cheska, Lester will</i>
<i>never hurt anyone again. I promise.</i>

229
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:21,449
<i>Your brother is sick.</i>

230
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:24,118
<i>My son's not the first</i>
<i>person he's hurt here in Amurao!</i>

231
00:12:24,785 --> 00:12:29,457
<i>Mark my words,</i>
<i>one day, he will kill someone!</i>

232
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,167
<i>Please, Miss Cheska.</i>

233
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:34,837
<i>Louisa, you're a good kid.</i>

234
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:37,173
<i>You're the only good</i>
<i>one among your siblings.</i>

235
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:38,799
<i>When your parents left you,</i>

236
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:40,676
<i>I felt sorry for you.</i>

237
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:44,305
<i>But Lester needs to learn his lesson.</i>

238
00:12:44,388 --> 00:12:47,183
<i>Miss Cheska, Lester can't go to jail.</i>

239
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:49,727
<i>My siblings and I only have each other.</i>

240
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,604
<i>You know that.</i>

241
00:12:51,687 --> 00:12:54,106
<i>I am begging you, Miss Cheska.</i>

242
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:58,736
<i>I need my big brother, Miss Cheska.</i>

243
00:12:58,819 --> 00:13:03,657
[pensive music playing]

244
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:05,743
<i>Lester!</i>

245
00:13:06,535 --> 00:13:07,453
<i>Lester!</i>

246
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:08,412
[Louisa exhales heavily]

247
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:09,580
<i>Thank goodness.</i>

248
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:11,957
<i>I didn't think</i>
<i>Miss Cheska would hear me out.</i>

249
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,543
<i>You begged them?</i>

250
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,045
<i>You shouldn't have done that.</i>

251
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:18,506
<i>Look, if I hadn't done that,</i>
<i>you would've ended up in jail.</i>

252
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:21,133
<i>Do you know what</i>
<i>her stupid son said about our mother?</i>

253
00:13:21,717 --> 00:13:22,718
<i>So what?!</i>

254
00:13:22,801 --> 00:13:24,803
<i>Everything's been said</i>
<i>about our mother already!</i>

255
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:25,971
<i>You should've let it go!</i>

256
00:13:26,514 --> 00:13:29,892
<i>Don't you care if you go to prison?</i>
<i>Do you even think about us?</i>

257
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:31,727
<i>Such a drama queen.</i>

258
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:34,104
<i>You should be in showbiz.</i>

259
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:36,148
<i>You're so dramatic.</i>

260
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,775
[somber music playing]

261
00:13:37,858 --> 00:13:39,902
<i>Are you ever going</i>
<i>to take things seriously?</i>

262
00:13:40,736 --> 00:13:41,695
<i>You're too sensitive.</i>

263
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:43,864
<i>- Learn to chill out, Louisa.</i>
- [sighs exasperatedly]

264
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:46,242
[Lester] <i>Louisa, where are you going?</i>

265
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:48,369
<i>Hey! Louisa!</i>

266
00:13:48,452 --> 00:13:49,870
<i>Come on, it's just a joke!</i>

267
00:13:49,954 --> 00:13:50,871
<i>Louisa!</i>

268
00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:53,999
I thought she would grow old…

269
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:57,545
worrying about me and our brother.

270
00:13:57,628 --> 00:13:59,838
[somber music continues]

271
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:03,926
If you hadn't started asking around,

272
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,554
I wouldn't have known that…

273
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:09,181
that my dear sister had fallen in love.

274
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:14,520
And that there was
someone who truly loved her.

275
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:17,940
[somber music continues]

276
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:20,359
You still haven't stopped
searching for answers, huh?

277
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,279
But what if…

278
00:14:23,362 --> 00:14:27,366
we had the answer from the start?

279
00:14:30,494 --> 00:14:36,208
[somber music continues]

280
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:37,877
I've been pretty sure for a long time

281
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:40,254
that Edong wasn't
the one who killed Louisa.

282
00:14:42,256 --> 00:14:43,632
But if I'm wrong,

283
00:14:45,384 --> 00:14:46,635
then so be it.

284
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:50,514
What is important,

285
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:52,558
is that we uncover the truth.

286
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:55,352
[somber music continues]

287
00:14:55,436 --> 00:14:56,937
That's what Louisa deserves.

288
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:04,695
A lot of people didn't like her back then.

289
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:08,449
Not just because of our parents.

290
00:15:09,366 --> 00:15:11,327
My brother and
I really didn't help either.

291
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:12,536
[sniffling]

292
00:15:14,371 --> 00:15:15,789
In fact, we only added…

293
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,251
to the reasons for her to be judged

294
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:23,839
and rejected by the people of Amurao.

295
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,174
[music fades]

296
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:28,218
[breath quivers]

297
00:15:28,302 --> 00:15:29,678
Anyway… [sniffling]

298
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:30,888
Uh…

299
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:35,059
If I think of something useful,

300
00:15:35,851 --> 00:15:37,102
I'll give you a call.

301
00:15:37,978 --> 00:15:39,021
Thank you.

302
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:41,190
[solemn music playing]

303
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:42,816
[Lemuel] You and your brother…

304
00:15:43,984 --> 00:15:45,903
We share the same story.

305
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:49,949
Life was unfair to our siblings.

306
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,118
They never had the chance…

307
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:57,623
to change how people saw them.

308
00:16:00,584 --> 00:16:03,379
Now, we're the only
ones they can depend on

309
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:04,797
to do that for them.

310
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:09,802
[solemn music continues]

311
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:17,935
- [Liezel] <i>So, it wasn't Kyle?</i>
- [music fades]

312
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:21,105
Surely Erica won't let him
get away with the nonsense

313
00:16:21,188 --> 00:16:23,774
he's been running from in the US, right?

314
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:25,192
That, we can be sure of.

315
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:26,735
You know that woman.

316
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:28,445
I mean, I couldn't ever stop
her from breathing down my neck…

317
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:29,613
[male student 1] Dude, her boobs are huge!

318
00:16:29,697 --> 00:16:31,281
- What?
- [male student 2] Bouncy!

319
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:32,950
This is awesome, man! [chuckles]

320
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:36,078
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!
- [Liezel sighs]

321
00:16:36,161 --> 00:16:38,205
I see three male students in big trouble.

322
00:16:38,288 --> 00:16:39,999
You're seriously
watching this inside the school?

323
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:42,418
[male student 2] Ma'am! That's mine!

324
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:43,836
Give me back my phone!

325
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:46,380
You're causing me trauma!

326
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:48,215
I feel an anxiety attack coming!

327
00:16:48,298 --> 00:16:50,467
Really? Oh no!

328
00:16:50,551 --> 00:16:53,804
Let me see that anxiety attack of yours.

329
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:57,474
Ma'am! You're humiliating us!

330
00:16:57,558 --> 00:17:00,394
You're violating
the government child protection policy!

331
00:17:00,477 --> 00:17:02,187
[chuckles dryly] Wow, Amurao!

332
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:03,397
You've got that one memorized, huh?

333
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:05,899
But having the common sense that
watching porn at school is forbidden,

334
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:06,900
you don't.

335
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:09,445
And your basic respect for women? Zero.

336
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:10,487
[male student 2] Ma'am…

337
00:17:10,904 --> 00:17:12,823
The video was just sent to me, ma'am.

338
00:17:13,365 --> 00:17:15,117
It's already everywhere.

339
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,037
Is that really a valid
reason to watch this…

340
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:19,663
this…

341
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:25,085
[unsettling music playing]

342
00:17:31,091 --> 00:17:33,177
Expect to find yourselves
in the principal's office later.

343
00:17:33,802 --> 00:17:35,387
- Go to your class!
- Ma'am…

344
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:36,847
Now!

345
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:39,850
[hurried footsteps]

346
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:42,478
[unsettling music continues]

347
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:43,687
Beth?

348
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,439
What's that?

349
00:17:45,522 --> 00:17:48,901
[unsettling music swells, fades]

350
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:50,527
There are seats available for…

351
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:53,072
tomorrow.

352
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,198
Tomorrow?

353
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:58,368
[sighs heavily] Scott.

354
00:17:58,827 --> 00:18:00,537
We already talked about this.

355
00:18:02,331 --> 00:18:04,291
[breathes heavily]

356
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:06,251
I know.

357
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,462
I just didn't think it'd be…

358
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:10,339
this soon.

359
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:14,927
[tender music playing]

360
00:18:15,677 --> 00:18:16,678
[Alice sighs]

361
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:19,014
It has to be.

362
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:22,476
[sighs]

363
00:18:27,856 --> 00:18:29,024
[sighs deeply]

364
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:33,028
[music becomes unsettling]

365
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:37,991
[cell phone ringing]

366
00:18:45,165 --> 00:18:47,167
- Sorry.
- [ringing continues]

367
00:18:48,877 --> 00:18:50,337
[exhales deeply]

368
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:51,797
Beth?

369
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:55,050
What?

370
00:18:55,634 --> 00:18:57,427
Wh- What do you mean online?

371
00:18:58,011 --> 00:19:02,766
- "Controversy of the year!"
- [grim music playing]

372
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:09,940
"HEY! IT IS MEL MONTENEGRO
IN THAT SEX VIDEO!"

373
00:19:10,023 --> 00:19:12,568
"OMG! IS THE VIDEO LEGIT?"

374
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:14,903
"WAIT. I'LL SEND THE LINK."

375
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:24,121
"IT IS HER! I TOOK A SCREENSHOT!"

376
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:26,832
"IT'S GIVING REVENGE PORN."

377
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:29,668
"SO THAT'S WHY SHE'S M.I.A. LATELY."

378
00:19:29,751 --> 00:19:31,545
"THIS IS SO MESSY!"

379
00:19:31,628 --> 00:19:35,424
- "ANTON DESERVES BETTER."
- "DEEPFAKE? LOOKS REAL TO ME."

380
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:44,516
[unsettling music continues]

381
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:08,415
[unsettling music continues]

382
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:36,526
[music turns sinister]

383
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:55,254
- [phone chimes]
- "HEY… JUST SAW THE VIDEO. HOW ARE YOU?…"

384
00:21:02,552 --> 00:21:08,267
[sinister music intensifies]

385
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:19,736
"MEL MONTENEGRO'S
ACCOUNT HAS BEEN DEACTIVATED."

386
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:32,332
[chuckles softly, inhales deeply]

387
00:21:36,586 --> 00:21:38,046
Good girl.

388
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:42,259
[sinister music continues]

389
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:51,476
<i>They violated Mel and</i>
<i>you expect me to do nothing?!</i>

390
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:54,062
<i>I know you love Mel,</i>
<i>but what she needs now</i>

391
00:21:54,146 --> 00:21:55,731
<i>is to win her case against Anton.</i>

392
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:57,649
<i>This isn't about how I feel about Mel.</i>

393
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:59,484
<i>It's in the past.</i>
<i>I don't have feelings for her anymore.</i>

394
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:02,821
<i>I already told you</i>
<i>that I didn't want Lucas and I to be over.</i>

395
00:22:02,904 --> 00:22:04,406
<i>But still, you put yourself between us!</i>

396
00:22:04,489 --> 00:22:05,907
<i>You're fighting for</i>
<i>your life and your career.</i>

397
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:07,367
<i>Why are you focusing on me?!</i>

398
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:10,037
<i>You couldn't be content</i>
<i>by almost killing Mel, huh?</i>

399
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:12,039
<i>You had to humiliate her, too?!</i>

400
00:22:12,122 --> 00:22:14,875
<i>I'm going to ruin her until</i>
<i>no other man would want her.</i>

401
00:22:14,958 --> 00:22:15,834
<i>She's mine!</i>

402
00:22:15,917 --> 00:22:18,170
[Barbara]<i> Stop it!</i>
